```class Solution {
public:
    string shortestPalindrome(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        string result = "";
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            result += s[i];
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (s[j] != s[i]) {
                    result = result + s[j];
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
};```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the string from the last character to the first character (n - 1 to 0) and adds each character to the result string. Then, it iterates through the remaining characters (from the second character to the first character) and checks if the characters are different. If they are different, it adds the next character to the result string and breaks the loop. This process continues until a non-matching character is found or all characters are processed. The solution has a time complexity of O(n^2) because of the nested loops, but it uses a constant amount of space (O(1)) and has low energy implications.

